‚çù Hand-built binary EXIF fixtures for ParseEXIFTests.
‚çù
‚çù No third-party image library: every byte of the JPEG container, the embedded
‚çù TIFF header, the IFD entries and the RATIONALs is assembled here, so the
‚çù fixtures can be regenerated and diffed. Run from anywhere:
‚çù     dyalogscript apl-service/tests/fixtures/exif/generate_fixtures.apls
‚çù
‚çù ‚éïIO‚Üê0 throughout so byte offsets index arrays directly.

‚éïIO‚Üê0

‚çù Output directory is this script's own directory.
args‚Üê2 ‚éïNQ'.' 'GetCommandLineArgs'
scriptPath‚Üê‚äÉ(‚à®/¬®'.apls'‚àò‚ç∑¬®args)/args
OutDir‚Üê‚äÉ1 ‚éïNPARTS scriptPath

‚çù EncLE/EncBE: encode a non-negative integer into ‚ç∫ bytes, little-/big-endian.
‚çù ‚ä§ yields most-significant byte first; little-endian reverses that.
EncLE‚Üê{‚åΩ(‚ç∫‚ç¥256)‚ä§‚çµ}
EncBE‚Üê{(‚ç∫‚ç¥256)‚ä§‚çµ}

‚çù A 12-byte IFD entry: (tag type count) Entry valueOrOffsetBytes.
‚çù The value/offset field must already be exactly 4 bytes. Making Entry dyadic
‚çù keeps the scalar (tag type count) tuple and the byte vector in separate
‚çù arguments: a bare strand mixing them would silently nest the vector.
Entry‚Üê{(tag type count)‚Üê‚ç∫ ‚ãÑ (2 EncLE tag),(2 EncLE type),(4 EncLE count),‚çµ}

‚çù An 8-byte TIFF RATIONAL: numerator Rational denominator, each a 4-byte LONG.
Rational‚Üê{(4 EncLE ‚ç∫),(4 EncLE ‚çµ)}

‚çù Overwrite ‚â¢new bytes at offset off. ‚ç∫ is (off new); ‚çµ is the original.
Patch‚Üê{(off new)‚Üê‚ç∫ ‚ãÑ (off‚Üë‚çµ),new,((off+‚â¢new)‚Üì‚çµ)}

‚àá ok‚Üêfn WriteBytes bytes;tie;signed
‚çù Write unsigned 0..255 byte values. ‚éïNAPPEND type 83 is signed 8-bit, so
‚çù fold 128..255 into their negative two's-complement counterparts first.
  :Trap 0 ‚ãÑ 1 ‚éïNDELETE fn ‚ãÑ :Else ‚ãÑ :EndTrap
  tie‚Üêfn ‚éïNCREATE 0
  signed‚Üêbytes-256√óbytes>127
  {}signed ‚éïNAPPEND tie 83
  {}‚éïNUNTIE tie
  ok‚Üê1
‚àá

‚çù --- The well-formed TIFF payload (little-endian, "II") -------------------
‚çù Offsets below are relative to the TIFF header start. IFD0 holds Make, Model,
‚çù Orientation and the Exif/GPS sub-IFD pointers; the Exif and GPS IFDs follow
‚çù in the data area. Every offset is stated as a named constant and the blocks
‚çù are concatenated in the same order, so the layout is checked by construction.

mkOff‚Üê74            ‚çù Make string, right after IFD0
mdOff‚Üê81            ‚çù Model string
exifIFDOff‚Üê89       ‚çù Exif sub-IFD
dtoOff‚Üê131          ‚çù DateTimeOriginal string
gpsIFDOff‚Üê151       ‚çù GPS sub-IFD
latOff‚Üê205          ‚çù GPSLatitude rationals
lonOff‚Üê229          ‚çù GPSLongitude rationals

tiffHeader‚Üê(‚éïUCS'II'),(2 EncLE 42),(4 EncLE 8)

ifd0‚Üê2 EncLE 5
ifd0,‚Üê(271 2 7)Entry(4 EncLE mkOff)          ‚çù Make        0x010F ASCII
ifd0,‚Üê(272 2 8)Entry(4 EncLE mdOff)          ‚çù Model       0x0110 ASCII
ifd0,‚Üê(274 3 1)Entry((2 EncLE 1),0 0)        ‚çù Orientation 0x0112 SHORT, inline
ifd0,‚Üê(34665 4 1)Entry(4 EncLE exifIFDOff)   ‚çù ExifIFD     0x8769 LONG pointer
ifd0,‚Üê(34853 4 1)Entry(4 EncLE gpsIFDOff)    ‚çù GPSInfoIFD  0x8825 LONG pointer
ifd0,‚Üê4 EncLE 0                              ‚çù no next IFD

makeStr‚Üê(‚éïUCS'Dyalog'),0
modelStr‚Üê(‚éïUCS'TestCam'),0

exifIFD‚Üê2 EncLE 3
exifIFD,‚Üê(36867 2 20)Entry(4 EncLE dtoOff)   ‚çù DateTimeOriginal 0x9003 ASCII
exifIFD,‚Üê(40962 4 1)Entry(4 EncLE 800)       ‚çù ExifImageWidth   0xA002 LONG, inline
exifIFD,‚Üê(40963 4 1)Entry(4 EncLE 600)       ‚çù ExifImageHeight  0xA003 LONG, inline
exifIFD,‚Üê4 EncLE 0

dtoStr‚Üê(‚éïUCS'2026:07:10 12:34:56'),0         ‚çù 19 chars + NUL = 20 bytes

gpsIFD‚Üê2 EncLE 4
gpsIFD,‚Üê(1 2 2)Entry((‚éïUCS'N'),0 0 0)        ‚çù GPSLatitudeRef  ASCII "N", inline
gpsIFD,‚Üê(2 5 3)Entry(4 EncLE latOff)         ‚çù GPSLatitude     3 RATIONALs
gpsIFD,‚Üê(3 2 2)Entry((‚éïUCS'W'),0 0 0)        ‚çù GPSLongitudeRef ASCII "W", inline
gpsIFD,‚Üê(4 5 3)Entry(4 EncLE lonOff)         ‚çù GPSLongitude    3 RATIONALs
gpsIFD,‚Üê4 EncLE 0

‚çù 51 deg 30 min 0 sec N = +51.5 ; 0 deg 7 min 30 sec W = -0.125
latData‚Üê(51 Rational 1),(30 Rational 1),(0 Rational 1)
lonData‚Üê(0 Rational 1),(7 Rational 1),(30 Rational 1)

tiff‚ÜêtiffHeader,ifd0,makeStr,modelStr,exifIFD,dtoStr,gpsIFD,latData,lonData

‚çù --- Wrap the TIFF in a JPEG APP1 segment ---------------------------------
‚çù SOI, APP1 marker, big-endian segment length (counts itself + payload),
‚çù the "Exif\0\0" identifier, the TIFF payload, then EOI. JPEG segment lengths
‚çù are always big-endian regardless of the TIFF byte order inside.
Wrap‚Üê{
    payload‚Üê(‚éïUCS'Exif'),0 0,‚çµ
    255 216,255 225,(2 EncBE(2+‚â¢payload)),payload,255 217
}

baseJpeg‚ÜêWrap tiff
tiffAt‚Üê12    ‚çù JPEG byte index of TIFF offset 0

‚çù --- The seven fixtures ---------------------------------------------------

withExif‚ÜêbaseJpeg

‚çù Byte-order marker corrupted to neither "II" nor "MM".
malformedTiff‚Üê(tiffAt)(‚éïUCS'XY')Patch baseJpeg

‚çù Make's value/offset field (TIFF offset 18) points far past EOF; every other
‚çù entry is intact, so only Make should come back empty.
outOfBounds‚Üê(tiffAt+18)(4 EncLE 60000)Patch baseJpeg

‚çù GPSLatitude's first RATIONAL denominator (TIFF offset 209) zeroed.
zeroDenomGps‚Üê(tiffAt+209)(4 EncLE 0)Patch baseJpeg

‚çù Truncated mid-IFD0: TIFF header and IFD0 entry count survive, but the file
‚çù ends before the five declared entries fit.
truncated‚Üê40‚ÜëbaseJpeg

‚çù Valid JPEG carrying only an APP0/JFIF segment, no APP1.
app0‚Üê(‚éïUCS'JFIF'),0,(1 1 0 0 1 0 1 0 0)
noExif‚Üê255 216,255 224,(2 EncBE(2+‚â¢app0)),app0,255 217

‚çù PNG signature: first two bytes are not the JPEG SOI.
notImage‚Üê137 80 78 71 13 10 26 10,(‚éïUCS'IHDR'),0 0 0 13

Fixtures‚Üê('with_exif.jpg'withExif)('no_exif.jpg'noExif)('not_an_image.png'notImage)('corrupt_truncated.jpg'truncated)('malformed_tiff_header.jpg'malformedTiff)('out_of_bounds_ifd0.jpg'outOfBounds)('zero_denominator_gps.jpg'zeroDenomGps)

:For fx :In Fixtures
    (name bytes)‚Üêfx
    {}(OutDir,name)WriteBytes bytes
    ‚éï‚Üê'wrote ',name,' (',(‚çï‚â¢bytes),' bytes)'
:EndFor

‚çù --- Independent self-check on the primary fixture ------------------------
‚çù Read with_exif.jpg back and decode Make directly (no ParseEXIF), confirming
‚çù the well-formed fixture's layout is internally consistent.
tie‚Üê(OutDir,'with_exif.jpg')‚éïNTIE 0
raw‚Üê256|‚éïNREAD tie 83(‚éïNSIZE tie)0
{}‚éïNUNTIE tie
makeBack‚Üê‚éïUCS raw[(tiffAt+mkOff)+‚ç≥6]
‚éï‚Üê'self-check Make = ',makeBack,(makeBack‚â°'Dyalog')‚äÉ(' MISMATCH')(' ok')
